  "prompt": "How do I get on the board of directors for a non-profit?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to get on a non-profit board:\n\n1. Develop relevant skills and experience\n- Demonstrate expertise in areas like finance, law, marketing, fundraising\n- Have leadership experience\n- Understand the non-profit's mission and work\n\n2. Network and build relationships\n- Attend non-profit events\n- Volunteer with the organization\n- Connect with current board members\n- Join professional associations related to the non-profit's field\n\n3. Show your commitment\n- Become an active volunteer\n- Make financial contributions\n- Demonstrate passion for the organization's mission\n\n4. Research board opportunities\n- Check the organization's website\n- Look for board recruitment announcements\n- Ask about board openings during interactions with the organization\n\n5. Prepare a strong application/proposal\n- Highlight your relevant skills and experience\n- Explain why you're interested in serving\n- Showcase your potential value to the board\n\n6. Be patient and persistent\n- Board positions can be competitive\n- Consider starting on a committee first\n- Keep building relationships and demonstrating your value\n\n7. Meet formal requirements\n- Some boards have specific qualifications\n- Be prepared to commit time and potentially make financial contributions\n- Pass background checks if required\n\nRemember that board selection processes vary by organization.",
